                  <Abstract ID="Abs1" Language="En">

                     <Heading>Abstract.</Heading>

                     <Para> The aim of this paper is to obtain quasimodes for a Schrödinger type operator <Emphasis Type="Italic">P</Emphasis>

                        <Subscript>

                           <Emphasis Type="Italic">h</Emphasis>

                        </Subscript> in a semi-classical limit <InlineEquation ID="Equ1">

                           <EquationSource Format="TEX">
$ (h \searrow 0) $</EquationSource>

                        </InlineEquation> with exponentially small error terms which are associated with Gevrey families of KAM tori of its principal symbol <Emphasis Type="Italic">H</Emphasis>. To do this we construct a Gevrey quantum Birkhoff normal form of <Emphasis Type="Italic">P</Emphasis>

                        <Subscript>

                           <Emphasis Type="Italic">h</Emphasis>

                        </Subscript> around the union <InlineEquation ID="Equ2">

                           <EquationSource Format="TEX">
$ \Lambda $</EquationSource>

                        </InlineEquation> of the KAM tori starting from a suitable Birkhoff normal form of <Emphasis Type="Italic">H</Emphasis> around <InlineEquation ID="Equ3">

                           <EquationSource Format="TEX">
$ \Lambda $</EquationSource>

                        </InlineEquation>. As an application we prove sharp lower bounds for the number of resonances of <Emphasis Type="Italic">P</Emphasis>

                        <Subscript>

                           <Emphasis Type="Italic">h</Emphasis>

                        </Subscript> defined by complex scaling which are exponentially close to the real axis. Applications to the discrete spectrum are also obtained.</Para>

                  </Abstract>

